for _ in range(int(input())):
    n = int(input())
    lis = []
    for i in range(n):
        lis.append(str(input()))
    a = lis.count('cakewalk')
    b = lis.count('simple')
    c = lis.count('easy')
    d = lis.count('easy-medium') + lis.count('medium')
    e = lis.count('medium-hard') + lis.count('hard')
    if a != 0 and b != 0 and (c != 0) and (d != 0) and (e != 0):
        print('Yes')
    else:
        print('No')
